dct_title_s: A new map of Germany, Hungary, Transilvania & the Suisse cantons : with many remarks not extant in any map
dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. Dedication: To His Grace John Duke of Marleborough, Prince of Mindelheim &c. this map of Germany &c. is most humbly dedicated by H. Moll Geographer. Note: The rout of ye Duke of Marlbrough's march into Germany is taken from ye journal of ye Quarter Master General by his Grace's special command. Inset: The General Diet of the Empire, or it's Parliament. Historic Maps copy has pencil annotations.
dct_publisher_sm: [London] : Printed for H. Moll between Temple Bar & St. Clements Church in ye Strand, I. Bowles Print and Map Seller over aginst Stocks Market and by P. Overton Mapp & Print seller near St. Dunstans Church in Fleet Street, and T. Bowles Print & Mapp seller next to ye Chapter house in St. Pauls Church yard, 1712.
